<div id="review_3373132769" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3373132769" />
    <a title="Donald Powell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15249098-donald-powell"><img alt="Donald Powell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1533766872p2/15249098.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3373132769?book_show_action=true">Jun 09, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Donald Powell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Donald Powell" href="/user/show/15249098-donald-powell">Donald Powell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780393340662" href="/book/show/10856622-the-fiery-trial">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15249098-donald-powell?shelf=biography">biography</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15249098-donald-powell?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15249098-donald-powell?shelf=government">government</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3373132769" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer391801097818242358">This is a Pulitzer Prize winning book specifically about Abraham Lincoln and his evolution about slavery and racism. This is an extensive, almost comprehensive, analysis of these matters. It would serve as a text for an upper level course on such topics. It is written with a master historian&apos;s balance and objectivity, revealing more about Lincoln than I had realized after reading quite a bit about him. He comes through as a real person, real politician and not the &quot;saint&quot; of whom he is popularly</span>
  <span id="freeText391801097818242358" style="display:none">This is a Pulitzer Prize winning book specifically about Abraham Lincoln and his evolution about slavery and racism. This is an extensive, almost comprehensive, analysis of these matters. It would serve as a text for an upper level course on such topics. It is written with a master historian's balance and objectivity, revealing more about Lincoln than I had realized after reading quite a bit about him. He comes through as a real person, real politician and not the "saint" of whom he is popularly portrayed. <br /><br />Given current events it gave me goose bumps to read some of what is recorded in this book. We are still living, struggling, suffering with the issues which resulted in the horrors of the civil war and all of the injustice which has transpired since. It is very sad and discouraging that ignorance, hate and injustice persist so dreadfully.</span>
  <a data-text-id="391801097818242358" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


