<span id="freeTextContainer3945449769234770603">Not quite a biography, but a life story of Lincoln&apos;s encounters with slavery. Of course, he is known as the Great Emancipator, but like all humans and serious issues, the story is more complicated and not always as pleasant as we wish it was. Lincoln was better than most of his contemporaries on the issue of slavery, but never where we wished he would be from our modern sensibilities. That&apos;s as it should be: progress means addressing the flaws of the past. Foner is a great writer and gives Linco</span>
  <span id="freeText3945449769234770603" style="display:none">Not quite a biography, but a life story of Lincoln's encounters with slavery. Of course, he is known as the Great Emancipator, but like all humans and serious issues, the story is more complicated and not always as pleasant as we wish it was. Lincoln was better than most of his contemporaries on the issue of slavery, but never where we wished he would be from our modern sensibilities. That's as it should be: progress means addressing the flaws of the past. Foner is a great writer and gives Lincoln a fair shake. In looking back, it's still obvious that the US is lucky to have had Lincoln as leader, but plenty of people can rightfully wish he was better. </span>
